                        </extent>
                        <condition key="other">
                           <p>The scroll shows some traces of use. Its upper outer part turned brownish; the right edge is affected by water. The red and yellow colours have faded away. The top and bottom are covered with dirt. The end of Texts X and XIII is unreadable.</p>
                           
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <ab type="ruling">Unruled</ab>
                        </layout>
                        <layout>
                           <p>Two columns</p>
                           
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">19th – early 20th-century script;  mediocre but careful hand.<note>
                           <p>Unknown</p>
                           
                        </note>
                        <note>
                           <p>“Brillenbuchstaben” in Texts I, VII, XI. The text columns are embraced with a yellow-and-black frame, along the edges of the scroll.</p>
                        </note>
                        <seg type="rubrication"/>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="other" xml:id="d2"/>
                     <decoNote type="mixed" xml:id="d3">
                        <p>Three fine polychrome pictures (black, yellow, red):</p>
                        <p>
                           <locus target="#1"/>) An angel with a sword and scabbard, at the top of the scroll</p>
                        <p>
                           <locus target="#2"/>) Standing cross (the Holy Cross?) with two birds sitting on the bar, two human figures standing below</p>
                        <p>
                           <locus target="#3"/>) A face in the middle of a cross, framed by four panels with stylized human faces (“The Net of Solomon”), under column <locus target="#2"/>.</p>
                        
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <p>በስመ፡አብ፡"... ጸሎት፡በእንተ፡ሕማመ፡ዓይነ፡ጥላ፡ወዓይነ፡ወርቅ፡ዓይነት፡ባርያ፡ወዓይነ፡አጋንንት፡ቁረኛ፡ወተያያዢ፡ጅን፡ ወያባስ፡ ባርያ፡ወሌጌዎን፡...</p>
                           
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">
                           <p>Scroll made of four pieces of parchment (ca. <locus target="#51 #50 #46"/>.<locus target="#5"/>and <locus target="#42"/>cm long) sewn together with narrow leather strips.</p>
                           <p>Remains of a leather strip which was inserted in the upper edge of the scroll.</p>
                           
                        </decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
